I'm building a Kratos user service. I need to handle these error cases: user not found (HTTP 404), duplicate username (HTTP 409), and invalid email format (HTTP 400). Currently I'm defining errors like this in my biz layer:

```go
// internal/biz/user.go
package biz

import kratosErrors "github.com/go-kratos/kratos/v2/errors"

var (
    ErrUserNotFound = kratosErrors.NotFound("USER_NOT_FOUND", "user not found")
    ErrDuplicateUser = kratosErrors.Conflict("DUPLICATE_USER", "username already exists")
    ErrInvalidEmail = kratosErrors.BadRequest("INVALID_EMAIL", "email format is invalid")
)
```

And returning them directly from my service layer:

```go
// internal/service/user.go
func (s *UserService) CreateUser(ctx context.Context, req *v1.CreateUserRequest) (*v1.CreateUserReply, error) {
    user, err := s.uc.CreateUser(ctx, req)
    if err != nil {
        return nil, err  // returning biz errors directly
    }
    return &v1.CreateUserReply{User: toProtoUser(user)}, nil
}
```

Is this the right way to handle errors in Kratos? What should I change?
